sql:
SELECT session_name, AVG(duration) AS average_duration
FROM session_types
GROUP BY session_name;

SELECT COUNT(*) 
FROM experiments 
WHERE system_id = (SELECT system_id FROM systems WHERE system_name = 'fcOIS2');

external_knowledge:
- "Most successful experiments" refers to those with the highest number of successful runs (`good_runs`); 
- "Top 3" refers to the ranking by successful runs in descending order, with the highest ranked experiments first; 
- "Conducted in 2017" refers to the date range '2017-01-01' to '2017-12-31'.
